<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-8D5DE88A-1C44-447A-B5F5-135D3A8159A9" version="1" lang="en-US"?><tsTroubleshooting xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-8D5DE88A-1C44-447A-B5F5-135D3A8159A9" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" domains="(topic tsTroubleshooting)                            (topic hi-d)    (topic sdlVariables-c)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c tsTroubleshooting oceTroubleshooting-c)   " class="- topic/topic tsTroubleshooting/tsTroubleshooting "><title class="- topic/title ">How to send data to S&amp;S Venlo</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><tsBody class="- topic/body tsTroubleshooting/tsBody "><tsSymptoms id="M148151-B8" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsSymptoms "><p class="- topic/p ">In case HQ requests specific data (AllTraceData.zip, customer's print files, …), then please provide it as follows: 
</p><ul id="UL_DB9A3C0318DE48BA8D276415BB50EAE1" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_FDC813866509404F92315724262D558A" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Gather all requested data in a zip file. 
</p></li><li id="LI_92EBCE70D1E447A9BF6F6B2D7B5C8773" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Set the filename to &lt;<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">NSO</b>&gt;_&lt;<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">customer</b>&gt;_&lt;<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">serial number</b>&gt;<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">.zip</b> 
</p></li><li id="LI_964C774677274D258CCAAC8A117128CC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to 
<xref href="https://sftexternal.cpp.canon" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot gentext?>https://sftexternal.cpp.canon</xref> and login as sps-es (password: support) 
</p></li><li id="LI_8B4AD2EF14254BD09EDFAC92295371D4" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Upload the zip file into the root (do not create any directories) 
</p></li></ul><note id="M148151-NOE9" type="note" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">You can write in this directory, but you cannot read the content. This means you will not see your file after uploading is done. However, if you don't see any error messages, the upload should be okay. 
</p></note></tsSymptoms></tsBody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-5C937DF0-2BDD-497B-B1AC-3013A8804D24.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
